<p>Use the <code>.greyscale-[value]</code> utilities to apply a
grayscale filter to an element. This is useful for desaturating images,
icons, or backgrounds for stylistic or accessibility purposes.</p>
<h3 id="doc-syntax">Syntax</h3>
<pre class="html"><code>.greyscale-[value]</code></pre>
<p>This sets:</p>
<pre class="css"><code>filter: grayscale([value]);</code></pre>
<p>You can also apply these effects on hover using:</p>
<pre class="html"><code>.hover:greyscale-[value]</code></pre>
<p>Which sets the filter on hover only.</p>
<h3 id="doc-example">Example</h3>
<p><img class="w-max-500px mt-4 rounded greyscale-50 hover:greyscale-0" src="/images/color-image.jpg"></p>
<pre class="html"><code>&lt;img class=&quot;greyscale-50 hover:greyscale-0&quot; src=&quot;image.jpg&quot;&gt;</code></pre>
<p>This example shows a fully grayscale image that returns to color on
hover.</p>
